closed_prs.title: Ryan/fix unload other jit model message type + tests
closed_prs.body:
Issue: when emitting unloadingOtherJITMode, we were only emitting model namespace specific model info. However, it is possible for an LLM to evict an non-LLM model, this type should not be model namespace specific. The evicted model can be any of the ModelInstanceInfo.

Also restructured a lot of tests. Moved speculative decoding test out of respond. Added speculative decoding test for .complete. And also added initial tests for embedding models.

There is also unfortunately some typescript dark magic involved. This is because we are essentially creating different model backend interfaces that has different types for `ModelInfo` and `ModelInstanceInfo` depending on the concrete model backend interface (for example, for LLM, it will be LLMInfo and LLMInstanceInfo). However, to properly type this, we need higher order types, i.e. the `createBaseModelBackendInterface` returns a type that can then be filled in with the concrete types. This is unfortunately not possible with TypeScript. We are currently emulating this by:

1. First having the `createBaseModelBackendInterface` return types with "holes". Specifically, using with types "SpecificModelInstanceInfo" and "SpecificModelInfo"
2. When concrete backend interfaces are created, use `DeepReplaceType2` to replace "SpecificModelInstanceInfo" and "SpecificModelInfo" with actual concrete types.

Luckily this only affects TypeScript + only affects the llm namespace and embedding namespace.

Also added countTokens to embedding models.

closed_prs.title: First wave of automated tests with an actual LLM
closed_prs.body:
Switched to `@swc/jest` for about 11x speed up (take that, speculative decoding)

Added new type of "heavy tests" denoted by ".heavy.test.ts". These do not run in regular `npm run test`, and only runs with `npm run test-full`. Running heavy tests requires LM Studio to be running. (and also have qwen2.5 instruct 0.5B installed + no model default configs)

Decided to use jest's snapshot capturing:

- Much easier to write tests as the expected cases are generated automatically
- Much easier to update tests if we change implementation
- Also prevents us having to hardcode a lot of model metadata within test code ourselves

opened_issues.title: GPU offloading proper number
opened_issues.body:
Hi,

I have a model that I usually have to use in llama-cpp because of the proper number of GPU offloading.

Example, in the model in the image below, LM Studio allows me in configuration to select GPU offloading from 0 to 40.
If I select 40, I see in the logs, that it offloaded 41/41 layers to GPU.
If I select 39 in the configuration, it shows in the logs that it offloaded 39/41 layers to GPU.

**How do I offload 40/41 layers to the GPU? I can do this in llama-cpp directly.**

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4d591a06-93de-474f-ac91-4b933049f0e8)


Thanks for LM Studio!

opened_issues.title: Incorrect API mapping for bge-reranker-v2-m3 model
opened_issues.body:
Hi there,
I'm encountering an issue when using lm studio to start the API service. The bge-reranker-v2-m3 model is being mapped to the "/v1/embeddings" interface instead of the "/v1/rerank" interface. This is causing a problem for me as I'm unable to import the model in a rerank manner in Dify.

It would be great if you could consider adding the "/v1/rerank" API interface in future updates. This would greatly improve the functionality and compatibility of the model with different tools like Dify.

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/85f61905-3c5a-4ae5-bdfb-3ca94ee02297)

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/cb1cf771-4445-41b1-8a5c-7306b8b2431e)

- **Testing Improvements**: A significant focus was on expanding test coverage. PR #246 introduced the fourth wave of tests, covering remaining prediction methods, while PR #234 initiated automated testing with an LLM, significantly speeding up the process using `@swc/jest` and introducing "heavy tests" for comprehensive evaluation.
- **Open Issues**: Two critical issues were raised: Issue #252 concerns GPU
